{
  "stem": "4967.1",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 13.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "It was made in Germany.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "But when the Germans occupied us, they took it away from me.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And this was-- when, when the Russian came, the Jewish people were very pleased about it because they actually thought the Germans would occupy us because of disagreement between Poland, Germany, and Russia.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "But we didn't know how long the Russians would be staying in Lithuania.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "A year later, the German bombed us.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And we were occupied by the Germans two weeks after the bombing.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And when the Germans bombed us, five o'clock at night, you know, in the morning, and they bombed all the cities in the Baltic States.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And it took them 10 or 12 days to occupy, to come to us.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "But in the meantime, the Lithuanians start to slaughter the Jewish people.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "Our neighbor downstairs, which was one of the biggest [NON-ENGLISH]-- it means against the Jewish.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "[NON-ENGLISH] was an organization that didn't like the Jewish people, and didn't like the Russians.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "They came to us and they say, Drehspuls, you can't stay in your flat.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "You'll stay in my flat because there's going to be pogroms.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "And we stayed in his flat, I think for a week or 10 days.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "And were shooting.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "And then came in the Germans.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "But before the Germans came in, those [NON-ENGLISH], the green uniform civilian Lithuanians, which hated the Jews very much, arrested the Jewish people, shot them, and took them to the Ninth and Seventh fort.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "It's a fortress place where there used to be garrisons of army and so on before.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "And the Jewish people used to lie there under the sky for days.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 15,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "And they used to have a machine gun that used to shoot at them.",
      "word_count": 14
    }
  ],
